
[1]ament

   AM'ENT, n. [L. amentum, a thong, or strap.]

   A botany, a species of inflorescence, from a common, chaffy receptacle;
   or consisting of many scales, ranged along a stalk or slender axis,
   which is the common receptacle; as in birch, oak, chestnut.
